‘No longer is a Mars flyby mission just one more theoretical idea. It can be done. Not in a matter of decades, but in a few years.’

The shuttle will be manned by one male and one female astronaut, both from America, although the names of the candidates have not been announced.

Tito’s mission will be financed from private donations, as well as support from government sources, and he is working with Nasa’s Ames Research Center and Applied Defense Solutions, among others.

